Module io.github.jonloucks.contracts.api
Package io.github.jonloucks.contracts.api

Class Contract<T>

java.lang.Object
io.github.jonloucks.contracts.api.Contract<T>
Type Parameters:
T - The type of deliverable
public final class Contract<T> extends Object
The API agreement for a Contract between the claimee and the claimant.

Each Contract instance is a unique key for establishing a binding between an implementation and those that use it.

  • Create by custom config create(Config)
  • Creation by automatic config. create(String, Object[])
  • Used by GlobalContracts.claimContract(Contract)
  • Used by GlobalContracts.bindContract(Contract, Promisor)
  • Used by Contracts.claim(Contract)
  • Used by Contracts.bind(Contract, Promisor)

A simple factory

Each call to Contracts.claim(Contract) will return a new instance. 
     
  // Save Contract at some agreed upon place
  public static final Contract<Contracts> SERVICE = Contract.create("You Choose");
  // The promisor needs to be bound before it is claimed.
  GlobalContracts.bindContract(SERVICE, () -> new ServiceImpl());
  // Ready to be claimed
  Contracts service = GlobalContracts.claimContract(SERVICE);
